# Class: <https://w3id.org/metpo/1003004> (obligately alkaliphilic)

AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00002022>) Annotation(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MICRO_0001565>) Annotation(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OMP_0005011>) Annotation(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OMP_0007771>) Annotation(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/OMP_0007947>) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/metpo/1003004> "An alkaliphilic phenotype in which an organism requires alkaline conditions (typically pH above 8.5) for growth and cannot grow at neutral or acidic pH.")
